description:
Here, we learn about the birth of Adventism in Australia. The work in Australia first began in Melbourne, and this is now known as the birthplace of Adventism. The missionaries started their work in tent meetings, and later progressed to creating a printing press and a health food company. God blessed these early sacrificial efforts of the early pioneers, and the work received a solid foundation.

To find out more information about the birth of Adventism in Australia  visit our website to read through our extended article.
